M||tx|When the us wants to op post-signup onboarding, us activation, first-run exp, or time-to-value. Also use when the us mentions "onboarding flow," "activation rate," "us activation," "first-run exp," "empty states," "onboarding checklist," "aha moment," "new us exp," "us aren't activating," "nobody completes setup," "lo activation rate," "us sign up but don't use the pd," "time to value," or "first sn exp." Use this whenever us are signing up but not sticking around. For signup/registration op, see signup-flow-cro. For ongoing em sequences, see em-sequence.
